{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771341634,"nonce":"+fuec9AnElX3y5f0ICnvsU24Cus=","title":"FOUC when using cancel button on department edit form","message":"Clicking 'Abbrechen' on /werkstaetten/:id/edit causes a flash of unstyled content (FOUC) and a browser warning: 'Layout was forced before the page was fully loaded.'\n\nRoot cause: The cancel button uses `link_to :back` which generates `javascript:history.back()`. This interacts badly with Turbo Drive - Turbo tries to restore from its page cache, and the cached snapshot renders before stylesheets are applied.\n\nFix: Replace `:back` with an explicit path (e.g. `borrowers_path`) in `app/views/departments/_form.html.erb` line 65.\n\nPre-existing since initial commit.","files":null}]}